User Stories (Incorporating Validation Feedback)

The user stories have been refined to improve clarity, testability, and specificity in the acceptance criteria while keeping the same scope and functionality defined in the business problem.

User Stories
1. Monitor Regulatory Updates

User Story 1

As a Compliance Officer,
I want the system to monitor relevant regulatory sources,
so that I can stay informed about new or modified compliance requirements.

Acceptance Criteria

The system retrieves updates from configured regulatory sources.

The system identifies new or modified regulatory requirements.

The system displays identified regulatory updates to the compliance officer for review.

2. Review Regulatory Changes

User Story 2

As a Compliance Analyst,
I want to review identified regulatory updates,
so that I can understand which regulatory changes may impact our organization.

Acceptance Criteria

The system presents identified regulatory updates in a structured format.

The compliance analyst can view details of each regulatory update.

The regulatory update information clearly indicates the relevant regulation being updated.

3. Generate Compliance Reports

User Story 3

As a Compliance Officer,
I want the system to generate structured compliance reports,
so that I can document the organization’s compliance status for audits.

Acceptance Criteria

The system compiles available compliance information and applicable regulatory requirements.

The system generates a structured compliance report.

The report summarizes applicable regulations and the organization’s current compliance status.

4. Detect Compliance Gaps

User Story 4

As a Compliance Analyst,
I want the system to identify potential compliance gaps,
so that I can address areas where current documentation or processes may not meet regulatory requirements.

Acceptance Criteria

The system analyzes regulatory requirements and available compliance information.

The system flags areas where regulatory requirements do not match existing compliance documentation.

The compliance analyst can review the identified compliance gaps.

5. Support Audit Preparation

User Story 5

As an Audit Manager,
I want access to compliance reports and identified compliance gaps,
so that I can prepare for internal or external compliance audits.

Acceptance Criteria

The audit manager can access generated compliance reports.

The audit manager can review identified compliance gaps.

The reports and identified gaps can be used as supporting material during audit preparation.